01/06/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Cyprus became the 23rd EU member to ratify the Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) between Albania and the EU on Friday (May 30th).
That same day, opposition Socialist Party leader Edi Rama unveiled a resolution his party intends to submit in parliament, insisting Albania apply for EU membership status by early autumn.
In other news, the Bulgarian parliament ratified Montenegro's SAA with the EU on Friday.
Bulgarian Ambassador to Montenegro Snejana Naydenova vowed that Sofia will be a constructive partner on Podgorica's road to Euro-Atlantic integration.
(Republika, Panorama, Focus - 31/05/08;
RTCG - 30/05/08)
